// Convergence-check rejection fixture.
//
// `convergence_ok` (structuring/mod.rs) gates the elision of tail `Jump`s from absorbed
// arms to hoisted orphans. It returns false when an absorbed arm has a CFG out-edge to a
// node in `start_subtree` that is *not* an orphan candidate (and not an escape / loop
// exit). Eliding in that case would silently rewrite the Jump as fall-through to the
// wrong place; the check forces the Jump to survive.
//
// CFG:
//
//        0 (cond) ── then ──> 1 (cond) ── then ──> 3 (code, -> 6)
//                ── else ──> 2 (code, -> 5)        └── else ──> 4 (code, -> 5)
//        5 sink
//        6 sink
//
// At node 0 the orphan-hoist absorbs arms 1 and 2 into an IfElse. 5 is an ichild of 0
// (preds 2, 4 — dom LCA = 0) and the planned hoist orphan. 6 is *not* an ichild of 0:
// its only predecessor is 3, so its idom is 3, not 0.
//
// absorbed_subtree = {0, 1, 2, 3, 4} (1's dom-children include 3 and 4 because each is
// reached only from 1). The edge 3 -> 6 leaves absorbed_subtree to a node that's in
// start_subtree but NOT in candidates ({5}). `convergence_ok` returns false → the
// orphan-hoist skips elision → the `Jump(_, 6)` from block 3 survives in the structured
// output.
//
// If someone later weakens `convergence_ok` (e.g. always returns true), the elision
// fires and the residual Jump disappears from the snapshot — this fixture catches that.

cond,0,1,2
cond,1,3,4
code,2,5
code,3,6
code,4,5
code,5
code,6
